HEADWORD: malignant melanoma
<hw>malignant melanoma</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <def>Any of
several malignant neoplasms (usually of the skin) consisting of
melanocytes; called also <altname>melanoma</altname>. It is classed as a
type of <isa>skin cancer</isa>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>malignant neoplasm</ent>⟦br⟧
